To help us understand the importance of firewalls in cybersecurity by 
designing and implementing a simple Linux firewall policy using UFW 
(Uncomplicated Firewall), then testing its effectiveness using tools from Kali 
Linux. 
Tools to be used are: Oracle virtual box, Kali Linux VM and Ubuntu VM 
Services to be used are: UFW, Nmap and SSH 
UFW (Uncomplicated Firewall) rules are specific instructions that dictate how 
the Uncomplicated Firewall (UFW) handle incoming and outgoing network 
traffic. They define which connections are allowed, denied, or limited based on 
various criteria like ports, protocols, and IP addresses. 
